│ when x==0. A conservative fix is to prevent ctpop comparison folds that depend on “ctpop < 2” / “ctpop == 1” when the ctpop call carries range metadata, because that       │
│ metadata exclusion of 0 is not guaranteed to be valid under all guards. I will modify foldICmpIntrinsicWithConstant to bail out early for ctpop when Pred is ULT with C==2  │
│ or equality with C==1 if the ctpop call has MD_range metadata, avoiding the unsafe transform.                                                                               │
